## Key performance choices made here

| Decision | Why it's fast |
|---|---|
| `LATEST_CAMERA_IMAGE` update mode | Skips frame queuing, processes newest frame only |
| Plane & depth detection disabled | Removes heavy computation you don't need |
| Light estimation disabled | Saves ~2ms per frame |
| YUV→NV21→JPEG at 85% quality | Faster than full decode, ARCore still tracks well |
| Scale bitmap to 320×240 before DB insert | Smaller = faster feature extraction |
| 30-frame cooldown | Prevents hammering the DB with re-registers |
| `addImage()` with physical width hint | ARCore finds features faster with real-world size |

The auto-focus AF state check is the trigger — the moment the device confirms sharp focus, it captures and locks. No button tap needed.